    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-05-31T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-05-31T10:00:00-05:00" n="650"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d650">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">751G.00/5–3154: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">United States Delegation</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-05-31T16:00:00+01:00"
                            >May 31, 1954—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Dulte1">Dulte</gloss> 135. Repeated information Paris 367,
                    Saigon 135. Re <gloss target="#t_Tosec1">Tosec</gloss> 269 (repeated Paris 4272
                    and Saigon 2418)<note n="1" xml:id="d650fn1">See footnote 1 to telegram <gloss
                            target="#t_Secto1">Secto</gloss> 331, <ref target="#pg_968">p.
                        968</ref>.</note> and Paris 4565 to Department (repeated Geneva 304 and
                    Saigon 549).<note n="2" xml:id="d650fn2">See <ref target="#pg_968">footnote 2,
                                <hi rend="italic">ibid</hi>
                        </ref>.</note> Am advised <persName corresp="#p_BG1">Bidault</persName>
                    wishes to discuss with me in near future question of clarifying independence. Am
                    told he is in general agreement with line of thinking <gloss target="#t_Tosec1"
                        >Tosec</gloss> 269 but has some ideas of his own on how to proceed.</p>
                <p>My own views remain those expressed in <gloss target="#t_Dulte1">Dulte</gloss>
                        120.<note n="3" xml:id="d650fn3">Dated May 26. <ref target="#pg_935">p.
                            935</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SWB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
